{
  "stem": "11771.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was sleeping, and I hear somebody slapping me for the foot.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I sit up.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "While I'm sitting up, feel with a stick over my head.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Wake up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'Documents.' I have not documents. 'Where are you?' I was half asleep and and, and, and confused already from the-- from the [INAUDIBLE] head.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, when a sleeping man comes up from sleep and suddenly you got a stick over your head, fast and hard.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I say, I'm from Ejszyszki. 'Dress up and come.'",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What happened that night, from Ejszyszki, a round-up waked up 100 people from the massacre, and they settled in Radun or in Voranava.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Now they came to Radun and Voranava.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were about 7, 10 kilometers from Ejszyszki, 13 kilometers from Ejszyszki.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they took back together all the refugees from Ejszyszki.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They took 100 people, refugees from Voranava.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In Radun, they were successful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was the action in the same night in Radun, too.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But in Radun, they were successful because they act better officially than the Voranava Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Everybody got registered as a Radun-- residents.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In Voranava they didn't do that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't know why-- because they were too sure with themselves, or whether because Hirsch [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Koppelman, ?] the head of Judenrat, had good connections with the Ju-- with the SS.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they took-- they put together 100 people from all over.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they took me, dressed up, from house to house, I go with them two going in the next house.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "One stays with me and is watching me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They put together about four or five-- four people, Jews who ran away from Ejszyszki or from Vilna, and they put it in Kommandatur-- from their Kommandatur.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
